'''High Galactic''' was a [[Pre-Republic era|Pre-Republic]] language which was later used to show respect for the clergy and the elite.

==History==
It was spoken by the colonists of [[Alsakan/Legends|Alsakan]] prior to [[17,000 BBY]]. During the war between the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] and the [[Tion Cluster/Legends|Tion Cluster]] it evolved its written form, the [[High Galactic/Legends|High Galactic alphabet]].<ref name="WW">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/source/writtenword/index.html?page=1|text=The Written Word|int=The Written Word}}</ref>

In later millennia, it was often used to show respect between members of the clergy and laymen. [[Sarcev Quest]] was fluent in High Galactic. It was also used as the language of the Imperial court and elite, as most officers from prestigious families were familiar with High Galactic.

Additionally, it was an ancient language used by the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]]. An example of this usage would be many of the names of their [[Lightsaber combat/Legends|lightsaber forms]].

Its alphabet became an alternative to [[Aurebesh/Legends|Aurebesh]] for written forms of [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Basic]].

==Derivatives==
The [[Nyriaanan|natives]] of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Nyriaan/Legends|Nyriaan]] spoke [[Nyriaanan (language)|Nyriaanan]], a language that was a mixture of High Galactic and Basic.<ref name="GOI">''[[Galaxy of Intrigue]]''</ref>

==Examples==
Example words included:
*[[Fi (High Galactic)|''Fi'']] - male child
*[[Pera (High Galactic)|''Pera'']] - male parent

==Behind the scenes==
High Galactic was first mentioned in [[Star Wars (1977)|Marvel's ''Star Wars'']] when [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] addressed an [[Pera|unnamed Verpine priest]].

